Key Match Events: The Rangers scored five runs in the second inning and five in the third inning to go up 10-0.
The D-backs scored six runs in the final two innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Outfielder Tommy Pham commented on the mood of the locker room, emphasizing the need to win every game now.
D-backs manager Torey Lovullo reflected on the challenges of getting the right matchups and executing them.
Closer Paul Sewald discussed the importance of playing loose and taking the game one inning at a time.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rangers are 10-0 on the road this postseason.
Despite losing Adolis García to injury, the Rangers have maintained a potent offense.
